In the version migration file (e.g., v1.rs), implement the UncheckedOnRuntimeUpgrade trait. This is the recommended approach because it will be wrapped with VersionedMigration for automatic version checking. Example migrating a StorageValue from u32 to a struct:

```rust
use frame_support::traits::UncheckedOnRuntimeUpgrade;

pub struct InnerMigrateV0ToV1<T: Config>(PhantomData<T>);

impl<T: Config> UncheckedOnRuntimeUpgrade for InnerMigrateV0ToV1<T> {
    fn on_runtime_upgrade() -> Weight {
        let old_value = frame_support::storage::unhashed::get::<u32>(
            &pallet::Value::<T>::hashed_key()
        ).unwrap_or_default();

        let new_value = CurrentAndPreviousValue {
            current: old_value,
            previous: None,
        };

        pallet::Value::<T>::put(new_value);

        T::DbWeight::get().reads_writes(1, 1)
    }
}
```

The on_runtime_upgrade function must: read existing storage in the old format, transform data to the new format, write updated values back, and return the consumed weight.

Add testing hooks to validate migration correctness. These only run in test/try-runtime environments, never on-chain:

```rust
impl<T: Config> UncheckedOnRuntimeUpgrade for InnerMigrateV0ToV1<T> {
    // ... on_runtime_upgrade from step 3 ...

    #[cfg(feature = "try-runtime")]
    fn pre_upgrade() -> Result<Vec<u8>, sp_runtime::TryRuntimeError> {
        let old_value = frame_support::storage::unhashed::get::<u32>(
            &pallet::Value::<T>::hashed_key()
        );
        Ok(old_value.encode())
    }

    #[cfg(feature = "try-runtime")]
    fn post_upgrade(state: Vec<u8>) -> Result<(), sp_runtime::TryRuntimeError> {
        let old_value = Option::<u32>::decode(&mut &state[..]).unwrap();
        let new_value = pallet::Value::<T>::get();
        assert_eq!(new_value.current, old_value.unwrap_or_default());
        assert_eq!(new_value.previous, None);
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

pre_upgrade captures state before migration; post_upgrade verifies the result. Neither should modify storage.

